About Our Client

Our client creating an industry 4.0 building system that allows every building component to be ordered and fabricated directly from factory. It aims to provide an Amazon-like experience for building projects to find, configure and manufacture building products at competitive prices on demand.

The embedded product finder and product configurator functions are powered by cutting edge machine learning and algorithmic models developed by the Data Science team. They are now hiring a Data Scientist to be a key contributor to this technology.

Job Description

Job Responsibilities:
• Conduct research and implementation of ML model;
• Engage in the design and implementation of ML service for our digital platform;
• Collaborate with various team for developing ML service;
• MLOps pipeline management;
• Engage in the end-to-end lifecycle of ML/DS service development and maintenance.

The Successful Applicant

Job Requirements:
• Bachelor/ Master degree in Mathematics... Computer Science/ Statistics or any relevant disciplines;
• At least 3+ years' experience in Machine Learning OR data science product development, preferably in computer vision, NLP, constraint optimization or reinforcement learning;
• Proficiency in Python, Bash, Git, Linux;
• Proficiency in Pytorch/ Pytorch-lightning/ Docker;
• Experience with MLOps will be a plus; (Optional);
• Good command of English, Cantonese and Mandarin.

