TCL is one of the world’s leading manufacturers of consumer electronic products, engaged in research & development, manufacturing and sales of TV and audio-video products with a global distribution sales network.
The Core Search & Recommendations team at TCL is looking for a (Senior)Data Scientist to help build the next generation of our TV search & recommendation engine. Our team creates internal analytical tools as well as users facing machine/deep learning models that enable TV media resource search and discovery. Our ideal candidate will be able to develop critical insights into our recommender engine data and make strategic recommendations on key opportunities, as well as grow out their skillset in the modeling space.
We’re seeking a strong data scientist candidate that is comfortable pulling and aggregating data from multiple large sources, building out models, designing strategies, defining KPIs, conducting A/B/n tests, and is interested in experimental design.
Job... description
1. Responsible for the optimization of the recommendation utility of TCL TV content business, and improving the product DAU/retention/time and other valuable metrics;
2. Explore various cutting-edge models, formulate appropriate algorithms and strategies for different business scenarios, continuously optimize effects and performance, and enhance user experience;
3. Participate in the construction of the algorithm-driven system of the core business (advertising/search/information flow), build a personalized recommendation system/advertising recommendation engine for the TV scene, and increase the advertising revenue and user activity of the Internet business;
4. Experiments on applying data mining, deep learning, machine learning algorithms into real industrial applications with millions of daily UV;
Job Requirements
1. Master's or PhD in Computer Science, Statistics, and other related majors;
2. Excellent coding ability, solid data structure, and algorithm skills;
3. Solid programming skills, familiar with programming languages such as python and scala.
4. Hands-on industry experience in big data processing filed such as Spark, HIVE, Elasticsearch, Redis etc.
5. Familiar with deep learning framework
All applications applied through our system will be delivered directly to the advertiser and privacy of personal data of the applicant will be ensured with security

About Our Client

Our client is a first unified automation company for health-care industry; They use machine learning approaches that focus on robotics technology for medical surgery.

They bring together the best of people, data and technology to efficiently, accurately and autonomously navigate the complex state of medical reimbursement. Currently, they're searching for several experienced C/ C++ engineer to join their tech R&D team.

Job Description
• Work closely with a live-production systems and product teams to understand user interest, user intent, improve content relevancy and deliver solutions;
• Responsible for system architecture software design and maintain the current sub systems;
• Perform system integration to optimise the current performance of the systems;
• Develop components, models and algorithms of the system;
• Create formal design documentations;

The Successful Applicant
• Bachelor's degree in Computer Science/ Electrical Engineering/ relevant field;
At least... 3-5 Years of experience in C/ C++/ Python programming for embedded system/ AI/ Machine learning platform;
• Strong OOP design with good debugging skill is essential.
• Strong experience in data structures and design patterns (Knowledge in database such as SQL server, MySQL, PostgreSQL ,Oracle.);
• Experience in real-time software operating systems and communication protocols would be an advantage;
• Knowledge in Data model language: XML, JSON, XDR, HTML (CSS).
• Good command of written and spoken in English

What's on Offer
• Competitive Salary;
• 14-15 Annual Leaves;
• Individual Performance Bonus.
• Fast-track promotion

